item.content:
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;General Tips:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Know the schedule&lt;/strong&gt;: Russian league starts like MLS. Don&amp;#39;t play any pre-season friendlies. Transfer window is mid-season, so buying youngsters that will improve from season-to-season is extra important.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Depth isn&amp;#39;t an Issue&lt;/strong&gt;: Because FIFA&amp;#39;s energy ratings aren&amp;#39;t realistic, you can play the same people every game, every week. All you need is a replacement for each position in case of injury or to bring off the bench. Less overall players means you can spend your salary money on better quality players.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;He&amp;#39;s LM, not LW:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;FIFA generally lets you use outside mids on either side without stat penalty (aka: inverted player). There&amp;#39;s no penalty for playing LW in a LM slot either. Because of this, we&amp;#39;ll be looking for a combination of pace, passing, and defending skill instead of ruling them out just based on what side they prefer. When possible play them on a preferred side, but it&amp;#39;s not mandatory.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;No GK Subs&lt;/strong&gt;: Your bench doesn&amp;#39;t need a GK on it. If your keeper gets hurt, let him play it out. Diversity of subs is more important than having a GK that you never, ever, ever sub in.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt;Year 1: Getting off the Mark&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Formation&lt;/strong&gt;: Use what you&amp;#39;ve got, and that&amp;#39;s attacking power and decent midfielders. Using a 3-4-1-2 formation suits the strengths of the initial roster. It&amp;#39;s ok to play a couple people slightly out of position until the transfer window. You&amp;#39;ll be playing at least one person out of position on purpose, but more on that below.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Play an attacking style&lt;/strong&gt;: The Russian league isn&amp;#39;t the Bundesliga in terms of quality. Having 3 strong players up-top allows enough ball movement to shred a computer&amp;#39;s back 4 (even on World Class) and just so happens to work well with 3-4-1-2.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Lots and Lots of Mids&lt;/strong&gt;: The trick to the formation is finding players (especially subs) that play well in multiple positions. An AM that also plays CM or Wing is more valuable. 3-4-1-2 uses 2 strikers, 2 outside mids, and 2 inside mids. Your bench of 5 only has room for 3 mids (assuming CB and ST are already there) which lets you have LM/RM, CM, and AM. Being able to move players around the pitch is crucial.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;But 3 at the Back?&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Yes, 3 defenders seems risky, but it&amp;#39;s crucial for success in manager mode. With 3 in the back, all of your defenders play the same position. LB or RB that are also good at CB, RM, LM, CM, or CDM can be used as a utility player or super-sub. Those that can&amp;#39;t play other positions can be sold. This lets you focus on having world-class CB, with 1 or 2 extras on your squad. You never need more than 1 CB on the bench for a game, which lets you focus on attacking subs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Strikers&lt;/strong&gt;: Hulk&amp;#39;s overall (82) jumps to 86 when played up top. Play him on the right and cut inside to shoot since he shanks every right-footed shot. Rondon &amp;amp; Kerzhakov both have above 80 pace and decent movement off the ball. Rotate them on the left. If you prefer giving all the XP to younger players, you can exclusively play Rondon &amp;amp; sell Kerzhakov for funds in Year 1 or 2.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Attacking Mid&lt;/strong&gt;: Danny Alves is the obvious choice.&amp;nbsp;Older players have cheap contracts, so hold onto him until his stats fade in Year 4 or (more likely) you buy a better AM.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Outside Mid&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;nbsp;Arshavin, Bystrov, Fayzulin, and Ryazantsev are the initial choices to fill the LM / RM slots. Play 2 and put the other 2 on the bench for depth/subs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Center Mid&lt;/strong&gt;: The obvious starters are Axel Witsel and Shirokov. Put Zyryanov on the bench.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;The Back Line&lt;/strong&gt;: Garay, Neto, Lombarts. Keep one of the LB/RB on the bench as a sub &amp;amp; another for injury cover. Feel free to sell the rest.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;strong&gt;Between the Posts&lt;/strong&gt;: Malafeev is fine for now. He won&amp;#39;t be the starter for very long.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
